				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Before you try pulling a lvl 65 high risk....<a name="32945"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 5 04 11:38 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>After losing my first two hard LDONs, I've been successful on 30 or 40 in a row.  My regular XP group are all ranked in the top 15 on Luclin Leader Board for hard ldon win % and I am that group's sole puller.  And we have a grand total of two Vex Thal items within that group, both of them on a wizard.  I have an unbuffed AC over 1400 now without ever having seen the inside of VT and without having made it to the Elemental Planes yet.  So the traditional approach to what gear is needed and where to get it is just that - a tradition.  Not a rule.  I also have most of the defensive AAs which probably matter more.  My general goal in LDON is to pull two at a time, one for the warrior to tank, one for me to mez.  My DPS output is the lowest of anyone in my group anyway - they're better off with me doing crowd control.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
