			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Before you try pulling a lvl 65 high risk....<a name="33429"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 7 04 3:56 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One of the tactics I like to use is to just mez a mob and let the other mobs chain aggro. If it looks like there are only two mobs who are linked I will mez one and then HOS/SLOW the non mezzed mob on the way back to camp. At camp I do standard twist until I see the message that mez has worn off. Then in 5 to 15 seconds I have an add. With a good DPS group, the first mob is just about dead at this point anyway. 
<br />

<br />
Pulls go very fast this way, AND your mana song is on the group longer too since there is less running out of camp to pull. In the event there are three mobs then I just bring the two non mezzed mobs and slow one of them and mez the other on the way back to camp. Now you can FADE if you don't want the first mezzed mob coming or just get ready to do some CC. 
<br />

<br />
Hope some of this is useful.
<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />
Torv Server
<br />
65 Bard</span></td>
