				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Before you try pulling a lvl 65 high risk....<a name="39920"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 14 04 7:41 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Group makeup and knowing what you're doing are the key things really. My usual line-up is:-
<br />

<br />
Me : SK (7500 HPs buffed) / Bard (5000 HPs buffed)
<br />
My sister: Cleric / Enchanter
<br />
Friend: SK / Shaman
<br />

<br />
With the exception of my SK, all are recently 65 in Bazaar gear with only a handful of AAs. My Bard has FM, Run3, Metab3, MC3 and that's it. She has her Epic and Composer Boots, everything else is hand-me-downs or Bazaar (well, the boots were Bazaar too<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />). My SK has 210 AA and a few raid items, mostly low end, wasn't much of a raiding fan 8-)
<br />

<br />
So, 3 players all 2-boxing relatively poor characters... hardly a recipie for success 8-)
<br />

<br />
We are all long-standing players though, we all started when EQ was originally launched, and my sister and friend have other chars that are 65 and well tooled up, as they liked to raid<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />My sister's Ranger tanks better than my SK 8-)
<br />

<br />
The make-up of the group also helps... 2 mezzers, 2 healers, 2 slowers (plus the Bard as a backup), 2 tanks, 2 forms of high mana regen... a backup for practically everything, so the loss of one character can be easily compensated for.
<br />

<br />
This allows a lot more flexibility in the pulling, 3 mobs is easy, 4 is ok, we can handle 5 at a push although we prefer not to if possible<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />I use a combo of the Bard and the SK to pull, identifying in advance what's coming and which char is handling which so the moment they step through the door they're all locked down. Lulls and FM are then really only needed for the big rooms 8-)
<br />

<br />
So, Hard LDoNs don't absolutely require uber chars to do them 8-)
<br />

<br />
I'd never dream of doing a Hard LDoN with a less ideal (or pickup) group though until my Bard is a LOT better equiped and AAd 8-)
<br />

<br />
Katawarl
<br />
</span></td>
