				<td colspan="2"><span>Your group sounds pretty similar to my regular hard ldon combo, Kata, except you have one extra member because I can't DW another char on my PC.  We generally have a Pal (tank) dwing an Ench, and a druid dwing a cleric.  We normally finish hards with 20ish minutes or so to spare, although those occasional HUGE EC zones can be very close.  Matter of fact, the only fails on hard we have, have been on the Arena of Chance zone (God I hate that zone)
<br />

<br />
None of us were VT+ equipped (things have changed recently, which makes it easier) but all of us are used to working together, and have been for years, which is what I feel makes all the difference.  When pulling I like to bring 2 if I can, 3 in a pinch, to save on wasted time pulling. The main part is educating them not to move up until I say so<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
