			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Before you try pulling a lvl 65 high risk....<a name="49934"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 3 04 1:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Okay so i pulled my first highrisk, let me tell you about it <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-7.gif" border="0" alt="Perplexed" hspace="2" />.
<br />

<br />
First, I didn't really want to. I figured my gear and AAs weren't good enough. BUT they talked me into it. To start with i had 5.5k and 0 defensive AAs. I did have FM and MC3, along with IM2 if it matters. 
<br />

<br />
Next, I'll admit it was an EC ldon and they're ridiculously easy to pull, but nonetheless! Group makeup was:
<br />
Me:65 bard
<br />
65 cleric
<br />
65 necro
<br />
65 warrior
<br />
59 rogue
<br />
65 bst
<br />

<br />
After talkin to another bard in tells(who has posted in this thread) I decided to give it a try. Song lineup;
<br />
RoT
<br />
snare
<br />
Mez
<br />
Veeshan
<br />
Rizlona's(no muse yet)
<br />
zek
<br />
marr
<br />
HoS
<br />

<br />
So we zone in and we're doin alright, no real hard splits of more than 2 mobs or maybe 3 once. Killing fast and everything. Haven't had to fade yet, cause 1 or 2 adds in camp isn't hard for me to handle and would rather save them. The bst says he's gotta go. Ooookay no more decent slows and dps is cut in half, with i think 13 drops to get in with 45 minutes to go. Some buffs broke and no bst to recast them so down to 5k. The warrior went down on a lucky quad followed by the rogue, but the necro managed to kite it around while the cleric clicked the warrior back in and we scaved a wipe. Then I died and got rezed and only had a virtue to work with so 4.2k is what I pulled 1/5 of the adventure with. We finished with about 10 minutes left on a collect 22.
<br />

<br />
On pulling it. It was suggested if your unsure how many are coming mez, i prefer proximity aggro. No bellow AA and no room in my lineup for one means if i mez and no adds come i can either wack it or i can sit there. Proximity aggro is great but have snare ready for Selo's mobs. I didn't fade once but I wouldn't have pulled without it. 
<br />

<br />
This is just a bit of hope out there to those that are newly dinged 65 that you CAN pull hards. I'm gonna do a few more ECs and then move on to EFs, and probably stop there until i get a few upgrades and more AAs.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
