				<td colspan="2"><span>The other night I got invited to pull a high risk MM.  Never one to shy away, I said yes and it went real well.  Then my usual group logged on and I asked if they wanted to do a high risk also and they said yes but wanted Tak.  It also went off well.  I will admit that I did die 5 times on bad pulls mainly when crit lull failure.  However, I had no FM, I only had 4900hp and a little over 1k ac.  Needless to say I'm very newb to 65.  My only point is that it is possible to pull high risks at a young age.
<br />

<br />
Btw, these boards are awesome.  I was definitely doing things the hard way trying to paci everything in sight.  Since then I have also gotten FM on the last high risk we did and tried it out towards the end.  Very nice!!  More aa, opening up Tak armor, and reading more on these boards will certainly make things easier though:)  s/f
<br />

<br />
Dromurr</span></td>
