				<td colspan="2"><span>Yea.  Defensive AAs are nice, but not necessary.  I only have CA2 + CS1, and truthfully, when I get caught, I am not sure more defensive AAs would help me anyway.
<br />

<br />
I try to save Fade for 4+ pulls (with FT6 only, I have to).  I figure if I pull 2.  I am golden.  1st mob is mezzed, pull 2nd to camp.  Go back and HoS/Snare 1st mob and walk it back to camp.
<br />

<br />
If I pull 3.  1st mob is mezzed, HoS/Snare mob 2 on way to camp.  Pull mob 3 to camp.  Run back to remez the snared mob 2.  Wait for mob 1 to wake up and remez or HoS/snare it.  Pull mob 1 or 2 to camp.  Go back and remez the remaining mob.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
